SEC. 8.

Election for Reserved Seats for Non-Metro Indigenous Peoples. -

Notwithstanding the immediately preceding sections, reserved seats for non-Moro indigenous peoples, such as Teduray, Lambangian, Dulangan Manobo, B'laan, and Higaonon, shall adhere to their customary laws and indigenous processes based on the following:

(a) Primacy of customary laws and practices;

(b) Primacy of consensus building;

(c) Acceptability to the community;

(d) Inclusive and full participation;

(e) Representation of the collective interests and aspirations of non-Moro indigenous peoples;

(f) Sustainability ans strengthening of indigenous political structures;

(g) Track record and capability; and

(h) Gender equality.

